name: r-reactable
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.3.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-reactable
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/reactable_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/reactable/reactable_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 38e4d49a235f6900e6d7dcb33245c925860edf0b3eb443c78ee0330b6a0c304d

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-digest
    - r-htmltools
    - r-htmlwidgets
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-reactr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-digest
    - r-htmltools
    - r-htmlwidgets
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-reactr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('reactable')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('reactable')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://glin.github.io/reactable, https://github.com/glin/reactable
  license: MIT
  summary: Interactive data tables for R, based on the 'React Table' JavaScript library. Provides an HTML widget that can be used in 'R Markdown' documents and 'Shiny' applications, or viewed from an R console.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
